		<h4>How much sales and use tax should be charged when a deal is redeemed?</h4>
		<p>States and cities often have complicated sales and use tax laws that may be confusing to you. Factors such as where you live, where you redeem your deal and for what goods or services you redeem it may affect how the deal is treated for purposes of taxation. It is every merchant’s responsibility to collect and remit tax as required by applicable law.</p>

		<h4>What if I change my mind and no longer want my Deal?</h4>
		<p>Good news! You can cancel or edit your own purchase up until midnight on the day you bought it! If you can no longer edit your own purchase, simply contact us at <a href="mailto:&#115;&#117;&#112;&#112;&#111;&#114;&#116;&#064;&#083;&#105;&#120;&#083;&#101;&#097;&#116;&#115;&#046;&#099;&#111;&#109;">&#115;&#117;&#112;&#112;&#111;&#114;&#116;&#064;&#083;&#105;&#120;&#083;&#101;&#097;&#116;&#115;&#046;&#099;&#111;&#109;</a> . Refund requests are handled on a case-by-case basis.</p>

		<h4>What if the business for my Deal closes down?</h4>
		<p>If anything happens that makes it impossible for you to redeem your Deal, we'll make sure you get your money back.</p>

		<h4>What happens if my Deal’s promotional value expires?</h4>
		<p>All is not lost! If your Deal's promotional value expires, you can always redeem it for the amount paid. For more information about expiration dates and voucher values, read our Terms of Sale</p>

		<h4>How will tickets be distributed and how will my seat be assigned?</h4>
		It depends. Read the offer’s Fine Print and other applicable terms carefully before you buy tickets. Tickets are usually distributed on a first-come, first-served basis at ticket pick up. Seating may be assigned on a first-purchased, first-served basis.

